Package: mortalityAdherence
Type: Package
Title: Biometric Table Adherence Testing for Pension Funds
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Eduardo Fraga L.", "de Melo", email = "eduardofraga@ime.uerj.br",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(Affiliation = "UERJ / FGV-EMAp / SUSEP")),
    person("Helton", "Graziadei", role = "aut",
           comment = c(Affiliation = "Federal University at Sao Carlos - UFSCar")),
    person("Rodrigo", "Targino", role = "aut",
           comment = c(Affiliation = "FGV-EMAp"))
  )
Description: Tools for actuaries to test the adherence of biometric mortality
    tables to observed data from pension funds. Implements 11 statistical tests:
    Kolmogorov-Smirnov (KS), Chi-Square, Wald Type I and II and Likelihood
    Ratio Tests (LRT) Type I and II under both Poisson and Negative Binomial
    models, and a Bayesian Credibility Interval test. Supports multi-year data
    in long (stacked) format, with automatic detection of repeated age groups.
    Includes a built-in database of 10 biometric tables used in the Brazilian
    actuarial market (AT-2000bm, AT-2000m, AT-49M, AT-55m, AT-83ms, GAM71m,
    GAM83m, BR-EMS2010, BR-EMS2015, BR-EMS2021). Based on the research paper:
    de Melo, Graziadei & Targino (2026) "Annuity Table Validation in Pension
    Funds: A Comparative Power Analysis of Goodness-of-Fit Tests"
    <https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=6668699>.
